stylometry: Statistical method that explains how much of the variability of a factor can be caused or explained by its relationship to another factor. Coefficient of determination is used in trend analysis. It is computed as a value between 0 and 1. 0 meaning 0 percent and 1 meaning 100 percent. The higher the value, the better the fit. Coefficient of determination is shown by "r2" because it is the square of the coefficient of correlation which is "r". The coefficient of determination is an important tool in determining the degree of linear-correlation of variables in a regression analysis.
